cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with training large deep learning models. It could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it discusses scaling efficiency and communication rescheduling. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as deep learning models are commonly used in these fields. Finally, it could also be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with optimizing neural network training.
